                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_dælīmon" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dælīmon</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>dælujmon</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бес</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>demon</q></abv:tr></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>ūmæn jæ bæx dælimonty xast ū — bīræǧʒærmttæj tærsgæ kæny</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>его конь взращен подземными духами, (поэтому) он боится волчьих шкур</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>his horse is raised by underground spirits, (therefore) he is afraid of wolf skins</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."/><biblScope>332</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Собственно ‘нижний (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_dæl-"/>) дух (%imon%i)’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 157</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>δαίμων καταχϑόνιοζ</w></mentioned>; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wælimon"/> | %iwælujmon%i ‘верхний дух’; но откуда %iī%i | %iuj%i? соединительный элемент? или под влиянием д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rujmon"/> ‘сказочное чудовище’? Слово *%imon%i ‘дух’ отдельно не существует, оно восстанавливается на основании вышеприведенных слов и из сопоставления с <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>manah-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>manas-</w> <gloss><q>дух</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mainyu-</w> <gloss><q>дух</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>бестелесое существо</q></gloss></mentioned>, а также опираясь на <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>manó</w> <gloss><q>бес</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><w/> <gloss><q>демон</q></gloss></mentioned>, которое %sМunkácsi%s считает усвоенным из аланского. Полной ясности нет.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 157</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Munkácsi._ÁKE"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">457 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">457 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">29 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">29 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><author>Schmidt</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_FUF"/><biblScope>XVIII %i2%i 95, XIX %i2%i 19</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is literally ‘lower (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_dæl-"/>) spirit (%imon%i)’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 157</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>δαίμων καταχϑόνιοζ</w></mentioned>; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wælimon"/> | %iwælujmon%i ‘upper spirit’; but where does %iī%i | %iuj%i come from? linking morpheme? or the influence of Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rujmon"/> ‘fantastic beast’? The word *%imon%i ‘spirit’ does not exist as a separate word, it is reconstructed on the ground of the words above and because of comparison with <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>manah-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>manas-</w> <gloss><q>spirit</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>mainyu-</w> <gloss><q>spirit</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>immaterial creature</q></gloss></mentioned>, and also on the ground of <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>manó</w> <gloss><q>demon</q></gloss></mentioned>, which %sМunkácsi%s considers borrowed from Alan. There is no full clearness.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 157</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Munkácsi._ÁKE"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">457 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">457 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">29 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">29 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><author>Schmidt</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_FUF"/><biblScope>XVIII %i2%i 95, XIX %i2%i 19</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>